import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='size', kde=True, color='blue')
    median_size = data['size'].median()
    plt.axvline(median_size, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Median: {median_size:.2f}')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of the size of the nodes in the flare.json dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='depth', y='size', hue='depth', palette='viridis')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between the depth and the size of the nodes in the flare.json dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Depth', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['num_children'] = data['children'].apply(lambda x: len(x) if x else 0)
    ax = sns.histplot(data=data, x='num_children', bins=20, color='blue', kde=True)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of the number of children for each node in the flare.json dataset?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Number of Children")
    plt.ylabel("Frequency")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
